          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript employed as an instruction manual for performing Hindu rites of pūjā (worship) with food offerings and setting up images during the end of the month of Śukra (May/June), when the planet Venus is in transition, in order to alleviate or atone (prāyaścitta) the inauspicious and negative qualities associated with this period.</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Śukrāstapūjāvidhi</title>
              <title type="vernacular">शुक्रास्तपूजाविधि</title>
              <colophon>Colophon: iti śukrāstapūjāvidhiḥ samāptaḥ // (f. 2v).</colophon>
            </msItem>
